  "uuid": "pGze",
  "titre": "Décomposition en éléments simples",
  "theme": "fractions rationnelles",
  "auteur": "",
  "date": "",
  "organisation": "AMSCC",
  "contenu": [
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "Calculer la division euclidienne de $X^5+1$ par $X^4-2 X^3+X^2$."
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "$$\nX^5+1=(X+2) \\cdot\\left(X^4-2 X^3+X^2\\right)+3 X^3-2 X^2+1\n$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "Factoriser dans $\\mathbb{R}[X]$ le polynôme $X^4-2 X^3+X^2$."
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "$$\nX^4-2 X^3+X^2=X^2 \\cdot\\left(X^2-2 X+1\\right)=X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2\n$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "On note $F(X)=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^4-2 X^3+X^2}$. Donner la forme de la décomposition en éléments simples de $F(X)$ dans $\\mathbb{R}(X)$."
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "$$\nF(X)=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^4-2 X^3+X^2}=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2}=X+2+\\frac{A}{X}+\\frac{B}{X^2}+\\frac{C}{(X-1)}+\\frac{D}{(X-1)^2}\n$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "Calculer $\\lim\\limits_{X \\rightarrow 0}\\left(X^2 \\cdot F(X)\\right)$"
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\t\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 0}\\left(X^2 \\cdot F(X)\\right) & =\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 0} \\frac{X^2 \\cdot\\left(X^5+1\\right)}{X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2}=1 \\\\\n\t& =\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 0} X^2 \\cdot\\left[X+2+\\frac{A}{X}+\\frac{B}{X^2}+\\frac{C}{(X-1)}+\\frac{D}{(X-1)^2}\\right]=B\n\\end{aligned}\n$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "Calculer $\\lim\\limits_{X \\rightarrow 1}\\left((X-1)^2 \\cdot F(X)\\right)$."
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\t\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 1}\\left((X-1)^2 \\cdot F(X)\\right) & =\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 1} \\frac{(X A)^2 \\cdot\\left(X^5+1\\right)}{X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2}=2 \\\\\n\t& =\\lim _{X \\rightarrow 1}(X-1)^2 \\cdot\\left[X+2+\\frac{A}{X}+\\frac{B}{X^2}+\\frac{C}{(X-1)}+\\frac{D}{(X-1)^2}\\right]=D\n\\end{aligned}\n$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "Calculer $F(-1)$ et $F(2)$ de deux façons différentes."
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\t& F(-1)=\\frac{(-1)^5+1}{(-1)^2 \\cdot(-1-1)^2}=0 \\\\\n\t&=-1+2+\\frac{A}{-1}+\\frac{1}{(-1)^2}+\\frac{C}{(-1-1)}+\\frac{2}{(-1-1)^2}=2-A-\\frac{C}{2}+\\frac{1}{2} \\\\\n\t& \\Rightarrow 2 A+C=5 \\\\\n\t& F(2)=\\frac{(2)^5+1}{(2)^2 \\cdot(2-1)^2}=\\frac{33}{4} \\\\\n\t&=2+2+\\frac{A}{2}+\\frac{1}{(2)^2}+\\frac{C}{(2-1)}+\\frac{2}{(2-1)^2}=4+\\frac{A}{2}+\\frac{1}{4}+C+2 \\\\\n\t& \\Rightarrow A+2 C=4 \\\\\n\t&\\left\\{\\begin{array} { l } \n\t\t{ 2 A + C = 5 } \\\\\n\t\t{ A + 2 C = 4 }\n\t\\end{array} \\Leftrightarrow \\left\\{\\begin{array}{l}\n\t\tA=2 \\\\\n\t\tC=1\n\t\\end{array}\\right.\\right.\n\\end{aligned}\n$$"
    },
    {
      "type": "question",
      "value": "En déduire la décomposition en éléments simples de $F(X)$ dans $\\mathbb{R}(X)$."
    },
    {
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": "$$\nF(X)=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^4-2 X^3+X^2}=\\frac{X^5+1}{X^2 \\cdot(X-1)^2}=X+2+\\frac{2}{X}+\\frac{1}{X^2}+\\frac{1}{(X-1)}+\\frac{2}{(X-1)^2} .\n$$"
    }
  ]
}